---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { locales } from '../data/locales';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us - Free Online Screen"
  description="Learn more about Free Online Screen, our mission, features, and the premium technology stack behind our fullscreen utilities."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
  lang={locales.en.lang}
  locale="en"
>
  <section class="site-shell py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider">Our Story</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-5xl font-semibold leading-[0.95] text-balance text-ink md:text-6xl">About Us.</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-body text-balance">
        Free Online Screen is a collection of premium fullscreen utilities designed to transform any display into a dedicated workspace, diagnostic tool, or ambient surface.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-y border-hairline bg-canvas">
    <article class="rich-article site-shell max-w-3xl py-12 md:py-16">
      <h2>The Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Most fullscreen utilities on the web are cluttered with invasive advertisements, tracking cookies, and laggy rendering. We built <strong>Free Online Screen</strong> as a premium, fast, and completely distraction-free alternative.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you are testing a gaming monitor for dead pixels, setting up a relaxing ambient screensaver for study, playing a friendly prank on a coworker, or simulating updates for video production, our tools provide a flawless, high-fidelity experience.
      </p>

      <h2>Core Features</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
        <li><strong>Pure Color Screens</strong>: Open solid colors in fullscreen for screen cleaning, light painting, or checking color reproduction.</li>
        <li><strong>Display Diagnostics</strong>: Easily check and test screens for dead pixels or burn-in with precise color shifts.</li>
        <li><strong>Ambient Screensavers</strong>: Choose from a glassmorphic flip clock, matrix rain code, particle snow, gentle rain, fireplace, or deep space.</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic Prank Screens</strong>: Convincingly replicate system upgrade screens (Windows, macOS, Ubuntu, Android), radar sweeps, or retro crash screens.</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard Shortcuts</strong>: Fast controls block-wide (like pressing <kbd class="rounded border border-hairline px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs bg-canvas-soft">F</kbd> for fullscreen) allow rapid repeatability.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Privacy & Performance First</h2>
      <p>
        We respect your privacy. Everything runs entirely in your browser client-side. We do not set analytic track cookies or collect usage datasets. All animation frames render smoothly with specialized canvas and CSS layout logic, remaining performant across laptops, tablets, smart TVs, and mobile devices.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
